Description:
Internet à¤ªà¤° à¤Ÿà¥à¤°à¥‡à¤‚à¤¡ à¤•à¤°à¤¨à¥‡ à¤µà¤¾à¤²à¥‡ Data Analytics Course à¤•à¤¾ à¤ªà¥‚à¤°à¤¾ Roadmap | Data Analytics Kaise Bane? 

Welcome to our Data Analytics Complete Roadmap video! Are you ready to embark on an exciting journey into the world of data analytics? Whether you're a beginner or an experienced professional, this comprehensive guide is designed to equip you with the essential knowledge and skills needed to excel in the field of data analytics.

In this video, we will take you through a step-by-step roadmap that covers everything you need to know about data analytics. From understanding the fundamentals to mastering advanced techniques, we've got you covered. Our expert instructors will break down complex concepts into easy-to-understand modules, ensuring that you can follow along regardless of your prior experience.

Here's what you can expect from this video:

Introduction to Data Analytics: We'll start by laying a solid foundation, introducing you to the core concepts, terminologies, and key tools used in data analytics. You'll gain a clear understanding of why data analytics is crucial in today's data-driven world.

Data Collection and Preparation: Learn the art of collecting relevant data and preparing it for analysis. We'll explore different data sources, data cleaning techniques, and data transformation methods, ensuring that you have clean and reliable data for analysis.

Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA): Dive into the world of EDA, where we'll teach you how to extract valuable insights from your data. You'll learn how to visualize data, identify patterns, detect outliers, and draw meaningful conclusions.

Statistical Analysis and Modeling: Discover how to apply statistical techniques to analyze and interpret data effectively. We'll cover regression analysis, hypothesis testing, probability distributions, and more. Additionally, you'll gain hands-on experience in building predictive models using machine learning algorithms.

Data Visualization and Communication: Explore the power of data visualization in conveying your findings effectively. We'll demonstrate various visualization techniques and best practices, enabling you to create compelling visual representations of your data.

Advanced Analytics Techniques: Delve into advanced topics such as time series analysis, clustering, text mining, and social network analysis. You'll learn how to leverage these techniques to extract valuable insights from complex data sets.

Data Ethics and Privacy: Understand the ethical considerations and legal implications surrounding data analytics. We'll explore privacy concerns, data governance, and the responsible use of data to ensure that you approach data analytics in an ethical and responsible manner.

By the end of this video, you'll have a comprehensive understanding of data analytics and the skills needed to leverage data for informed decision-making. Whether you're aiming to enhance your career prospects, improve business outcomes, or simply satisfy your curiosity, this roadmap will be your ultimate guide.

So, what are you waiting for? Join us on this transformative journey into the world of data analytics. Hit the play button now and let's get started on your path to success!

Don't forget to like, comment, and subscribe to our channel for more valuable content on data analytics, machine learning, and the latest industry trends.

Note: This video is suitable for beginners as well as professionals looking to expand their knowledge in data analytics. No prior coding experience is required, but a basic understanding of statistics and mathematics will be beneficial.

Title: Should you take BTech in Data Science and Artificial Intelligence ? | Career Series
Description:
Pros and Cons of Pursuing a BTech in Data Science & AI: A Guide for High School Students with Online Course Recommendations
Are you a student considering a BTech in Data Science and AI? In this vlog, we explore the advantages and challenges of pursuing a degree in these fast-growing fields. We'll discuss the importance of foundational mathematics, aptitude, and genuine interest, as well as the career opportunities available to graduates. By understanding the pros and cons, you'll be better equipped to make an informed decision about your academic and career path.

In this vlog, you'll learn:

The key factors to consider before pursuing a BTech in Data Science and AI
The benefits of having a strong foundation in mathematics and the right aptitude for the subjects
The potential consequences of choosing a degree based on hype rather than genuine interest
How short online courses can help you assess your aptitude and passion for Data Science and AI, including recommendations like Coursera's "Introduction to AI" by IBM, edX's "CS50's Introduction to Artificial Intelligence with Python" by Harvard University, and Udacity's "Intro to Machine Learning with PyTorch and TensorFlow" Nanodegree program

Tips for making an informed decision on whether a BTech in Data Science and AI is right for you
Don't forget to like, comment, and subscribe for more insights on educational and career choices! #DataScience #ArtificialIntelligence #BTech #HighSchoolStudents #CareerGuidance #OnlineCourses

Title: Data Science Course and Market Condition in 2023.
Description:
There are several reasons why data science openings are less for freshers:

1. Lack of experience: Most companies prefer candidates with some experience in data science as it involves working with complex data sets, statistical models, and programming languages. Freshers may not have the required experience to handle these tasks.

2. High demand: Data science is a highly sought-after field, and there is a lot of competition for jobs. Companies receive a large number of applications for data science roles, and they tend to prefer candidates with some experience.

3. Skill gap: Many freshers may not have the necessary skills to succeed in data science roles. Data science requires a combination of technical skills, domain knowledge, and problem-solving abilities. Freshers may lack one or more of these skills.

4. Cost: Hiring and training freshers can be expensive for companies. They may prefer to hire experienced professionals who can hit the ground running and require less training.

Overall, while it may be challenging for freshers to find data science openings, there are still opportunities available. It is essential to focus on building the necessary skills and gaining experience through internships, projects, and certifications to increase your chances of landing a job in this field.

Title: Difference between Artificial Intelligence, Machine Learning, Deep Learning & Data Science
Description:
In this video, krish naik sir will clear up the confusion between Artificial Intelligence, Machine Learning, Deep Learning, and Data Science. You'll learn the key differences between each field and how they relate to one another. We'll start by defining AI, and how it is a broad field that simulates human intelligence in machines. We'll then delve into Machine Learning, which is a subset of AI, and how it allows systems to improve their performance by learning from data. Next, we'll take a look at Deep Learning, which is a subset of Machine Learning and how it uses neural networks to learn from large and complex data sets. Finally, we'll discuss Data Science, and how it uses a combination of mathematical and computational techniques to extract insights and knowledge from data. By the end of the video, you'll have a clear understanding of the relationship between AI, ML, DL, and Data Science, and how each field contributes to the development of intelligent systems.

Title: Data Analyst vs Data Scientist - What's the Difference? | Role, Skills, Salary & Demand
Description:
In this video, learn about Data Analyst vs Data Scientist - What's the Difference? | Role, Skills, Salary & Demand

Data Analysts and Data Scientists both work with data, but their roles and responsibilities differ.

Data Analysts focus on collecting, organizing, and analyzing data to support decision-making in a company. They create reports, visualizations, and dashboards to communicate insights to stakeholders.

Data Scientists use advanced statistical and machine-learning techniques to build predictive models and solve complex problems. They have a more advanced skill set and use their technical abilities to extract insights and value from data.

Skills for a Data Analyst typically include data visualization, SQL, and statistical analysis. Skills for a Data Scientist often include machine learning, programming (e.g. Python, R), and data engineering.

The salary for Data Analysts ranges from â‚¹2,30,000 to â‚¹8,30,000 per year, while Data Scientists can earn â‚¹3,30,000 to â‚¹15,30,000 per year or more.

The demand for both roles is growing, but the demand for Data Scientists is higher due to the increasing amount of data generated and the need for organizations to extract insights and value from it

Title: Statistics Roadmap for Data Science and Data Analysis | With Full Resources
Description:
Roadmap - https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/10spJMs0Zmv5cugfFjJVc4MudyOVjl_16Ef5z54oxqnM/edit?usp=sharing

Resources - https://docs.google.com/document/d/1GDKMZG5es9wkqk3ftiAXeUXKBc5fl0HlFIIKucPgRIs/edit?usp=sharing

Prepare to dive into the world of data like never before in our newest video, "Turning Digits into Decisions: The Essential Statistics Roadmap for Data Science". Whether you're a beginner just starting out or an experienced professional looking to brush up on your knowledge, this video provides a comprehensive yet easy-to-understand guide on how statistics drives the engine of data science.

Starting with the fundamentals, we will journey through the maze of statistical concepts and techniques that are critical for effective data analysis and prediction. From descriptive and inferential statistics to probability distributions and hypothesis testing, we unravel the intricate statistical methods that give you the power to make informed decisions.

This video doesn't just help you understand these key concepts; it brings them to life through real-world examples and hands-on exercises. Learn how to apply these tools and techniques in your everyday work, and unlock the true potential of data to transform your decisions.

Remember, it's not about the amount of data you have; it's about how you use it. So, join us as we turn digits into decisions, and transform your understanding of data science and statistics forever."

Title: Learn Data Science Tutorial - Full Course for Beginners
Description:
Learn Data Science is this full tutorial course for absolute beginners. Data science is considered the "sexiest job of the 21st century." You'll learn the important elements of data science. You'll be introduced to the principles, practices, and tools that make data science the powerful medium for critical insight in business and research. You'll have a solid foundation for future learning and applications in your work. With data science, you can do what you want to do, and do it better. This course covers the foundations of data science, data sourcing, coding, mathematics, and statistics.

Title: Difference between Artificial Intelligence, Machine Learning, Deep Learning & Data Science
Description:
In this video, krish naik sir will clear up the confusion between Artificial Intelligence, Machine Learning, Deep Learning, and Data Science. You'll learn the key differences between each field and how they relate to one another. We'll start by defining AI, and how it is a broad field that simulates human intelligence in machines. We'll then delve into Machine Learning, which is a subset of AI, and how it allows systems to improve their performance by learning from data. Next, we'll take a look at Deep Learning, which is a subset of Machine Learning and how it uses neural networks to learn from large and complex data sets. Finally, we'll discuss Data Science, and how it uses a combination of mathematical and computational techniques to extract insights and knowledge from data. By the end of the video, you'll have a clear understanding of the relationship between AI, ML, DL, and Data Science, and how each field contributes to the development of intelligent systems.

Title: Wie wird man Data Scientist?
Description:
Data Science, was ist das Ã¼berhaupt? Was macht ein Data Scientist? Was muss man lernen, wenn man eine Data Science Karriere anstrebt? Diese Fragen beantworte ich im heutigen Video.

Dem Beruf des Data Scientists wurde schon 2009 von Hal Varian und einige Jahre spÃ¤ter dem Harvard Business Review eine glorreiche Zukunft vorhergesagt. Diese Vorhersage ist eingetreten, Daten spielen eine wichtigere Rolle denn je, und Data Scientists sind auf dem Arbeitsmarkt extrem gefragt.

Data Science ist allerdings ein recht allgemeiner Begriff ("Wissenschaft mit Daten"), der sich in viele Unterbereiche aufgliedern lÃ¤sst, zum Beispiel: Messung & Metriken, Strategie, Vorhersagen (Time Series Analysis), Korrelationen, Experimente (AB-Tests), Data Engineering (Logging, ETL-Pipelines), Modellierung, Optimierung, Visualisierung, Maschinelles Lernen, KÃ¼nstliche Intelligenz.

Hinzu kommt, dass man sich mit jedem dieser Bereiche auf einer von drei Stufen beschÃ¤ftigen kann:
1) Grundlagenforschung (Level: Professor)
2) Angewandte Forschung bzw. Core Data Science (Level: PhD)
3) Anwendung bzw. Product Data Science (Level: Bachelor/Master/PhD)

Um als typischer Data Scientist in einer Firma zu arbeiten, sollte man mathematische Vorkenntnisse haben. Bewerber kommen Ã¼blicherweise aus Feldern wie: Informatik, Physik, Mathematik, Wirtschaftswissenschaften, Maschinenbau, Psychologie, ...

Vor allem die Statistik spielt in fast allen Bereichen eine immense Rolle. DarÃ¼ber hinaus ist ein guter Data Scientist mit Python und/oder R bewandert und hat gute KommunikationsfÃ¤higkeiten.

Peter Wang (GrÃ¼nder Anaconda) beantwortet die Frage "Was ist Data Science" so: data science is a literacy, not a job. Ihm zufolge entwickelt sich Data Science mehr und mehr zu einer allgemein notwendigen FÃ¤higkeit, die keinem einzelnen Berufszweig zuzuordnen ist.

Wenn du anfangen mÃ¶chtest, dich mit Data Science zu beschÃ¤ftigen, sind BÃ¼cher, Videos oder Vorlesungen zu Statistik und Python eine gute Wahl. FÃ¼r eine umfangende EinfÃ¼hrung empfehle ich Onlinekurse, z.B. den genannten von Coursera, siehe Link weiter unten.
